{{unreferenced|date=October 2008}} {{Campaignbox Hungary 1944–1945}} '''Operation Konrad''' was the [[Nazi Germany|German]]-[[Hungary|Hungarian]] effort to relieve the encircled garrison of [[Budapest]] during the [[Battle of Budapest]] in January 1945. The operation was divided into three parts:
* [[Operation Konrad I]] - 1 January 1945 - Led by [[IV SS Panzer Corps]] from [[Tata, Hungary|Tata]]. Halted near [[Bicske]]. * [[Operation Konrad II]] - 7 January 1945 - Led by IV SS Panzer Corps from [[Esztergom]]. Halted at [[Pilisszentkereszt]]. * [[Operation Konrad III]] - 17 January 1945 - Led by IV SS Panzer Corps and [[III Army Corps (Wehrmacht)|III Panzer Corps]] from south of Budapest near [[Székesfehérvár]]. Attempt to encircle ten [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] divisions. Halted south of [[Ercsi]].
==See also== * [[1st Panzer Division (Wehrmacht)|1st Panzer Division]] - Part of relief force * [[IV SS Panzer Corps]] - Part of relief force * [[III Panzer Corps (Wehrmacht)|III Panzer Corps]] - Part of relief force * [[IX Waffen Mountain Corps of the SS (Croatian)|IX SS Mountain Corps]] - Besieged in Budapest * [[Hungarian Third Army]] - Besieged in Budapest
